An unclosed literal opener !`oops leaks nothing.

This paragraph must stay *ordinary* prose, not literal content.

An unclosed math opener $`oops leaks nothing either.

This paragraph must stay /ordinary/ prose, not math content.

Closed forms still work: !`/kaet/` and $`x^2` and $$`E=mc^2`.

Multi-backtick fences: !``a`b`` and $``a`b``.

Attributes still attach: !`x`{.ipa} and $`y`{.big}.

Escaped bang is a plain code span: \!`x`.
